# Q1: Workspace routes/schemas duplicated between app and package

## Finding 1: Workspace routes duplicated (admin)
- File/lines: `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/workspace/routes/admin.routes.js:1`
- Source of truth should be: `packages/workspace/workspace-fastify-routes/src/shared/routes/admin.route.js`
- Shadow copy exists: full route list duplicated in app-local module
- Why risky: Any changes to permissions, auth, schemas, or paths in the package can drift from the app version, creating silent contract divergence between app and shared package clients.
- Suggested refactor: Delete the app-local route file and import `buildRoutes` from `@jskit-ai/workspace-fastify-routes` (or re-export it). If app-specific extensions are needed, wrap the package builder with a thin adapter that appends extra routes.

## Finding 2: Workspace routes duplicated (bootstrap)
- File/lines: `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/workspace/routes/bootstrap.routes.js:1`
- Source of truth should be: `packages/workspace/workspace-fastify-routes/src/shared/routes/bootstrap.route.js`
- Shadow copy exists: identical bootstrap route defined in app-local module
- Why risky: Public bootstrap contract can diverge from the shared package, leading to client/server mismatch and inconsistent validation.
- Suggested refactor: Replace app-local builder with direct import from the package and remove the duplicate.

## Finding 3: Workspace routes duplicated (self service)
- File/lines: `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/workspace/routes/selfService.routes.js:1`
- Source of truth should be: `packages/workspace/workspace-fastify-routes/src/shared/routes/selfService.route.js`
- Shadow copy exists: identical self-service route list defined in app-local module
- Why risky: Permissions or body/response schema updates in the package won’t propagate, causing inconsistent API behavior across deployments.
- Suggested refactor: Use the package route builder; keep only app-specific overrides via options.

## Finding 4: Workspace route assembly duplicated
- File/lines: `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/workspace/routes/index.js:1`
- Source of truth should be: `packages/workspace/workspace-fastify-routes/src/shared/routes.js`
- Shadow copy exists: app-local assembly of bootstrap/self-service/admin routes
- Why risky: Composition order or schema plumbing can diverge from package expectations; drift will be hard to detect.
- Suggested refactor: Re-export `buildRoutes` from package and pass app-specific `missingHandler` only.

## Finding 5: Workspace schema aggregation duplicated
- File/lines: `apps/jskit-value-app/server/modules/workspace/schemas/index.js:1`
- Source of truth should be: `packages/workspace/workspace-fastify-routes/src/shared/schema.js`
- Shadow copy exists: app-local schema composition
- Why risky: Schema composition changes in package won’t reach app; incorrect response/body validation is likely over time.
- Suggested refactor: Import `schema` from package and remove local index.

